INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (16,'Working with View Composers','working-with-view-composers','关于composer的简单教程','<iframe width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/IATAsQB31_o\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',3,'2016-10-23 07:53:00','2016-10-23 07:57:58',1,'2016-10-23 07:54:53',NULL),(18,'Doctor Strange Trade Show ','doctor-strange-trade-show','[無劇透]《奇異博士 Dr. Strange》短片試映 影評','<iframe width=100%  height=\"450\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/I4FxmAoyQSU\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',3,'2016-10-23 08:14:03','2016-10-23 21:24:42',1,'2016-10-23 08:19:47',NULL),(20,'Project Built with Laravel ','project-built-with-laravel','基于Laravel建造的开源应用','1. Vuedo\n\n	Vuedo是一个由Laravel和Vue.js构建的开源博客应用\n		\n		\n	传送门： https://github.com/Vuedo/vuedo\n		\n2. Canvas\n	 \n	 Canvas是一个为开发者提供的轻量级博客应用，致力于让博客变得简单、令人愉悦，Canvas使用了当下最新最流行的技术（基于Laravel 5.2）并且极力让后台变得简单，从而让作者把焦点放到写作上。\n	 \n	 传送门： https://github.com/austintoddj/canvas\n	 \n3. Attendize\n\n	Attendize 是基于 Laravel 框架开发的开源门票及活动管理应用。Attendize 用于为活动组织者管理活动提供一个简单的解决方案，不同组织者可以通过不同账户post各自活动， 系统也会为各个组织者做好相应的统计。 \n	\n	传送门： https://github.com/Attendize/Attendize\n	\n	官方网站：https://www.attendize.com\n	\n	演示页面：http://attendize.website/e/1/acmes-amazing-demo-event',3,'2016-10-31 01:40:14','2016-10-31 02:18:13',1,'2016-10-31 02:08:56',NULL),(21,'Euro Soccer Forever ','euro-soccer-forever','网页任意球小游戏','<div  style=\"margin-left:-15%\">\n	<!-- Place this code where you\'d like the game to appear -->\n<div class=\"miniclip-game-embed\" data-game-name=\"euro-soccer-forever\" data-theme=\"0\" data-width=\"960\" data-height=\"640\" data-language=\"en\"><a href=\"http://www.miniclip.com/games/euro-soccer-forever/\">Play Euro Soccer Forever</a></div>\n\n\n<!-- Insert this code before your </body> tag -->\n<script src=\"//static.miniclipcdn.com/js/game-embed.js\"></script>\n</div>\n\n',3,'2016-10-31 04:21:04','2016-10-31 04:57:29',1,'2016-10-31 04:22:17',NULL),(24,'Next Step','next-step-work','Some expectation ','1.  Add web game to game model \n\n2.  Seperate it with current post model\n\n3.  This part will be implemented by Vue js   ,vue waterfall \n\n4.   Backend would use current backend CRUD \n\n5.   Search good web game ',3,'2016-10-31 04:59:36','2016-10-31 05:16:02',1,'2016-10-31 05:04:16',NULL),(25,'Getting started with Vuejs','getting-started-with-vuejs','开始了解接触Vue.js','<iframe width=100% height=\"560\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/1CrZX259CXk\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',3,'2016-11-01 16:01:06','2016-11-01 16:09:20',1,'2016-11-01 16:09:20',NULL),(26,'Doctor Strange Easter Eggs','doctor-strange-easter-eggs','【彩蛋解析】奇異博士|奇異博士彩蛋|有雷(含劇透)|彩蛋解說奇異博士|萬人迷電影院|Doctor Strange Easter eggs','<iframe width=100% height=\"560\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/FDAxfPn2LcM\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',3,'2016-11-01 16:32:13','2016-11-01 16:33:41',1,'2016-11-01 16:33:41',NULL),(29,'Guardians of the Galaxy Second Trailer Analysis','guardians-of-the-galaxy-second-trailer-analysis','【預告分析+解說】星際異攻隊2|預告解析|角色介紹|銀河護衛隊2|銀河守護隊2|萬人迷電影院|Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2 trailer analysis','<iframe width=100% height=\"560\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/WfYDAPR7dqU\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',3,'2016-11-05 23:45:23','2016-11-05 23:47:25',1,'2016-11-05 23:47:25',NULL),(30,'How To Backup MySQL Databases on an Ubuntu','how-to-backup-mysql-databases-on-an-ubuntu','How To Backup MySQL Databases on an Ubuntu',' <h2>Backup a MySQL Database with mysqldump</h2>\n<pre>mysqldump -u <span class=\"highlight\">username</span> -p <span class=\"highlight\">database_to_backup</span> &gt; <span class=\"highlight\">backup_name</span>.sql\n\n</pre>\n<h2>Restoring</h2>\n<h4>step one :</h4>\n<pre>mysql -u <span class=\"highlight\">username</span> -p</pre>\n\n<h4>step two :</h4>\n\n\n<pre>CREATE DATABASE <span class=\"highlight\">database_name</span>;\nexit\n</pre>\n<h4>step three :</h4>\n\n\n<pre>mysql -u <span class=\"highlight\">username</span> -p <span class=\"highlight\">database_name</span> &lt; <span class=\"highlight\">backup_name</span>.sql</pre>\n\n<h4>Then,your information should now be restored to the database you\'ve created.</h4>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           | How To Backup MySQL Databases on an Ubuntu         |              | publish     | open           | open        |               | how-to-backup-mysql-databases-on-an-ubuntu        |         |        | 2016-06-05 19:02:31 | 2016-06-05 19:02:31 |                       |           0 | http://toogr8.com/?p=8                                 |          0 | post             |                |             0 |\n|  9 |           1 | 2016-06-05 18:36:10 | 2016-06-05 18:36:10 | <h2>Backup a MySQL Database with mysqldump</h2>\n<pre>mysqldump -u <span class=\"highlight\">username</span> -p <span class=\"highlight\">database_to_backup</span> &gt; <span class=\"highlight\">backup_name</span>.sql\n\n</pre>\n<h3><strong>Restoring</strong></h3>\nstep one :\n<pre>mysql -u <span class=\"highlight\">username</span> -p\n\nstep two :\n\n</pre>\n<pre>CREATE DATABASE <span class=\"highlight\">database_name</span>;\nexit\n\nstep three\n\n</pre>\n<pre>mysql -u <span class=\"highlight\">username</span> -p <span class=\"highlight\">database_name</span> &lt; <span class=\"highlight\">backup_name</span>.sql\n\nThen,your information should now be restored to the database you\'ve created.</pre> ',3,'2016-11-06 00:02:09','2016-11-06 00:05:41',1,'2016-11-06 00:03:56',NULL),(31,'How to install Nginx on CentOS','how-to-install-nginx-on-centos','How to install Nginx on CentOS','<h3 id=\"about-nginx\">About Nginx</h3>\nNginx is a high performance web server software. It is a much more flexible and lightweight program than Apache HTTP Server.\n\nThis tutorial will teach you how to install and start Nginx on your CentOS 7 server.\n<div data-unique=\"prerequisites\"></div>\n<h2 id=\"step-one—add-nginx-repository\">Step One—Add Nginx Repository</h2>\nTo add the CentOS 7 EPEL repository, open terminal and use the following command:\n<pre class=\"code-pre \">sudo yum install epel-release</pre>\n<div data-unique=\"step-two—install-nginx\"></div>\n<h2 id=\"step-two—install-nginx\">Step Two—Install Nginx</h2>\nNow that the Nginx repository is installed on your server, install Nginx using the following yum command:\n<pre class=\"code-pre \">sudo yum install nginx</pre>\nAfter you answer yes to the prompt, Nginx will finish installing on your virtual private server (VPS).\n<div data-unique=\"step-three—start-nginx\"></div>\n<h2 id=\"step-three—start-nginx\">Step Three—Start Nginx</h2>\nNginx does not start on its own. To get Nginx running, type:\n<pre class=\"code-pre \">sudo systemctl start nginx</pre>',3,'2016-11-06 00:06:17','2016-11-06 00:07:22',1,'2016-11-06 00:07:22',NULL),(32,'Vagrant and Ansible Quick Start  ','vagrant-and-ansible-quick-start','Vagrant & Ansible Quick Start  ',' <h2>Begin the vagrant config </h2>\n<pre>\nVagrant.configure(2) do |config|\n\nend\n</pre>\n\n<h2>Select Box</h2>\n<pre>\nconfig.vm.box=\"yourbox\"\n</pre>\n\n<h2>Synced your local folder with remote virtual server</h2>\n<pre>\nconfig.vm.synced_folder \"~/git/your_project\", \"/remote/folder\"\n</pre>\n<h2>Ansible provision</h2>\n<pre>\n  config.vm.provision \"ansible\" do |ansible|\n    ansible.groups = {\"server\" => [\"server\"], \"all_groups:children\" => [\"server\"]}\n    ansible.playbook = \"../ansible/playbooks/server-bootstrap.yml\"\n  end\n</pre>\n\n<h2>Trigger execute command </h2>\n<p>Before using trigger , you should install the vagrant trigger plugin</p>\n<pre>\n  config.trigger.after :up, :stdout => false do\n     run_remote \"cd /var/www/html\"  \n\n  end\n</pre>\n\n<p>To be continued </P>                                          ',3,'2016-11-06 01:07:03','2016-11-06 01:08:19',1,'2016-11-06 01:08:19',NULL),(33,'Required to use date.timezone setting','required-to-use-date-timezone-setting','Required to use date timezone setting',' <p>When i use composer install, it show me this error</p>\n\n<p>Finally i change the config in the php.ini fix this</p>\n\n<pre>\n[Date]\n; Defines the default timezone used by the date functions\n; http://php.net/date.timezone\ndate.timezone = [your time zone code ]\n</pre>\n\n<p>After that , please restart your server</p>\n\n<pre>\nsudo service httpd restart\n\nsudo service apache2 restart \n</pre>',3,'2016-11-06 01:10:22','2016-11-06 01:12:35',1,'2016-11-06 01:11:27',NULL),(34,'Solve Lumen migrate get user forge@localhost erro','solve-lumen-migrate-get-user-forgeatlocalhost-erro','Solve Lumen migrate get user forge@localhost erro','<p>I assume you guys are using Homestead and default database is mysql :)</p>\n\n<h2>database.php</h2>\n<p>In default Lumen , Lumen do not have database.php under config file.</p>\n<p>So we can copy the database.php from other laravel project</p>\n<p>You can copy code below and create /config/database.php</p>\n<pre>\n\n<?php\nreturn [\n    /*\n    |--------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    | PDO Fetch Style\n    |--------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    |\n    | By default, database results will be returned as instances of the PHP\n    | stdClass object; however, you may desire to retrieve records in an\n    | array format for simplicity. Here you can tweak the fetch style.\n    |\n    */\n    \'fetch\' => PDO::FETCH_CLASS,\n    /*\n    |--------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    | Default Database Connection Name\n    |--------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    |\n    | Here you may specify which of the database connections below you wish\n    | to use as your default connection for all database work. Of course\n    | you may use many connections at once using the Database library.\n    |\n    */\n    \'default\' => env(\'DB_CONNECTION\', \'mysql\'),\n    /*\n    |--------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    | Database Connections\n    |--------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    |\n    | Here are each of the database connections setup for your application.\n    | Of course, examples of configuring each database platform that is\n    | supported by Laravel is shown below to make development simple.\n    |\n    |\n    | All database work in Laravel is done through the PHP PDO facilities\n    | so make sure you have the driver for your particular database of\n    | choice installed on your machine before you begin development.\n    |\n    */\n    \'connections\' => [\n        \'sqlite\' => [\n            \'driver\' => \'sqlite\',\n            \'database\' => env(\'DB_DATABASE\', database_path(\'database.sqlite\')),\n            \'prefix\' => \'\',\n        ],\n        \'mysql\' => [\n            \'driver\' => \'mysql\',\n            \'host\' => env(\'DB_HOST\', \'localhost\'),\n            \'port\' => env(\'DB_PORT\', \'3306\'),\n            \'database\' => env(\'DB_DATABASE\', \'forge\'),\n            \'username\' => env(\'DB_USERNAME\', \'forge\'),\n            \'password\' => env(\'DB_PASSWORD\', \'\'),\n            \'charset\' => \'utf8\',\n            \'collation\' => \'utf8_unicode_ci\',\n            \'prefix\' => \'\',\n            \'strict\' => false,\n            \'engine\' => null,\n        ],\n        \'pgsql\' => [\n            \'driver\' => \'pgsql\',\n            \'host\' => env(\'DB_HOST\', \'localhost\'),\n            \'port\' => env(\'DB_PORT\', \'5432\'),\n            \'database\' => env(\'DB_DATABASE\', \'forge\'),\n            \'username\' => env(\'DB_USERNAME\', \'forge\'),\n            \'password\' => env(\'DB_PASSWORD\', \'\'),\n            \'charset\' => \'utf8\',\n            \'prefix\' => \'\',\n            \'schema\' => \'public\',\n        ],\n    ],\n    /*\n    |--------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    | Migration Repository Table\n    |--------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    |\n    | This table keeps track of all the migrations that have already run for\n    | your application. Using this information, we can determine which of\n    | the migrations on disk haven\'t actually been run in the database.\n    |\n    */\n    \'migrations\' => \'migrations\',\n    /*\n    |--------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    | Redis Databases\n    |--------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    |\n    | Redis is an open source, fast, and advanced key-value store that also\n    | provides a richer set of commands than a typical key-value systems\n    | such as APC or Memcached. Laravel makes it easy to dig right in.\n    |\n    */\n    \'redis\' => [\n        \'cluster\' => false,\n        \'default\' => [\n            \'host\' => env(\'REDIS_HOST\', \'localhost\'),\n            \'password\' => env(\'REDIS_PASSWORD\', null),\n            \'port\' => env(\'REDIS_PORT\', 6379),\n            \'database\' => 0,\n        ],\n    ],\n];\n\n</pre>\n<p>Remember change the database name,user and password in this file , then you can solve the problem</p>',3,'2016-11-06 01:22:05','2016-11-06 01:23:32',1,'2016-11-06 01:22:51',NULL),(37,'Convert Timezone in the Eloquent Query Builder ','convert-timezone-in-the-eloquent-query-builder','在Eloquent Query Builder里转换时间戳','Part one :  get timezone data in the request , and create convert_tz  sql  sentence used in the Eloquent Builder\n\nPart two : use query builder \n\n<pre>\n//part one\n$filter=[];\nif($request->has(\'timezone\'))\n{\n     $timezone=$request->input(\'timezone\');\n\n}else{\n     $timezone=\'+00:00\';\n}\n$convertSentence=\'convert_tz(bets.created_at,\"+00:00\",\"\'.$timezone.\'\") as bet_at\';\n$convertSentence=htmlspecialchars_decode($convertSentence,ENT_QUOTES);\n\n\n//part two\n\nreturn DB::table(\'bets\')\n                ->where($filter)\n                ->join(\'games\', \'bets.game_id\', \'=\', \'games.game_id\')\n                ->select(\'bets.username\',\'bets.bet\',\'bets.win\',\'bets.user_id\',\'games.name\',DB::raw($convertSentence))\n                ->paginate($pagination);\n\n\n</pre>',3,'2016-11-06 06:40:51','2016-11-06 06:49:50',1,'2016-11-06 06:49:50',NULL),(38,'Laravel Developer Interview Questions','laravel-developer-interview-questions','Several Laravel developer interview questions ','**1. Why you choose Laravel as your application framework ?**\n\na.  Dependency Injection is automating  dependency loading .\n\nb.  Artisan make development more efficient and productive .\n\nc.  Bundles and composer provide tremendous combination of modular packages .\n\nd. Eloquent ORM give us more support in the Database Operation like  query builder and get instance .  Relase us from old  school sql query generation  and pay more attention to elegant codes and logics .\n\n\n**2. What is your favourite feature of Laravel **\n\nPlease do not say \"It is easy to get started \".  There are many  Laravel related Tutorial on the Internet  and these bloggers also provide the project source code in the Github. \nYou can not convince other developer through familarity with those application code . \nActually , they are looking for something you got in the work.  \n\n\n**3. Have you used Lumen in your project ?**\n\nLumen is the micro-framework by Laravel that was made by Taylor specifically for APIs and microservices. Which means the project manager or director care about the performance issue.  \n\n\n**4. List some CLI in the artisan **\n\ntinker :  An excellent tool to test and operate Eloquent ORM. \n\nmigrate :  RDMS , when we need database , we will use it .\n\ndb:seeder :  populate the data in to specified table. \n\nlist :  sometimes  different team will customize the Laravel CLI , list can show you what command available in this box . \n\ndump autoload :  composer file changed and other modification , this command should be executed . \n\n\n**5. Laravel 5 has built in CSRF protection on every route. How would I go about turning that off?**\n\nHopefully they mention that CSRF protection is important, but since we\'re asking them to turn it off they might not mention it which is OK. You\'d easily turn it off by going into Kernel.php and removing it from the middleware stack that is ran on every route.\n\nThis is also a good place to ask about middleware in general and make sure they both understand what middleware is and why it\'s important.\n\n**6. Have you written any custom middleware for a Laravel applicaton? If so, tell me about a time you did.**\n\nFor instance , we will use JWT token in our normal request , we can add them in our service provider or app.php( Lumen ).  If the request dont have the jwt token , we can direct to error page or return json with the error message . \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n',3,'2016-11-07 01:28:58','2016-11-07 02:06:46',1,'2016-11-07 01:41:50',NULL),(39,'TwoSum Solution','twosum-solution','Program Interview Question Two Sum','# **Question:**\n\n**Given an array of integers, find two numbers such that they add up to a specific target number.\nThe function twoSum should return indices of the two numbers such that they add up to the target, where index1 must be less than index2. Please note that your returned answers (both index1 and index2) are not zero-based.\nYou may assume that each input would have exactly one solution.**\n\n\n# **Solution:**\n\n**HashMap is used to store the each number value and index\n\nnumber value is key in the map\n\nindex is value\n\nthen containsKey(minus result )\n\nwe will get two numers key\n\nget value for the index**\n\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\"> public int[] twoSum(int[] numbers,int target){  \n  //step two: create map  \n  Map&lt;Integer,Integer&gt; map =new HashMap&lt;&gt;();  \n  //step three: try to find the number  \n  for(int i=0;i&lt;numbers.length;i++){  \n   int x =numbers[i];  \n   if(map.containsKey(target-x)){  \n    return new int[]{map.get(target-x)+1,i+1};  \n   }  \n   map.put(x,i);  \n  }  \n  //step one : if no number match the condition  \n  throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"No number matches\");  \n }  \n</code></pre>\n\n\nRuntime  O(n)',3,'2016-11-07 07:12:34','2016-11-19 07:17:16',1,'2016-11-07 07:13:59',NULL),(40,'Two Sum II Solution','two-sum-ii-solution','Two Sum II Program Interview Question ','# **Question:**\n\n**Similar to Question [1. Two Sum], except that the input array is already sorted in ascending order.\n**\n# **Solution:**\n\n**array is sorted we should use this feature\n\ntwo pointer is better solution for this case**\n\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\"> public int[] twoSum(int[] numbers, int target) {  \n   // Assume input is already sorted.  \n   int i = 0, j = numbers.length - 1;  \n   while (i &lt; j) {  \n    int sum = numbers[i] + numbers[j];  \n    //sum less than target , mean i element is less  \n    //sorted , so next index must greater than i  \n    if (sum &lt; target) {  \n      i++;  \n    //sum greater than target , mean j is too greater  \n    //j-1 may be fit  \n    } else if (sum &gt; target) {  \n     j--;  \n    //sum=target , please get i and j both add 1  \n    } else {  \n     return new int[] { i + 1, j + 1 };  \n    }  \n   }  \n   //nothing matched  \n   throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"No number matches\");  \n }  \n</code></pre>\n\n',3,'2016-11-07 07:14:05','2016-11-19 07:16:27',1,'2016-11-07 07:15:20',NULL),(41,'ArrayList and StringBuffer Usage','arraylist-and-stringbuffer-usage','Learning Note ','**1. ArrayList or a dynamically resizing ArrayList:**\n\nIt is an array that resizes itself as needed while still providing O(1) access .\n\n\n**2. StringBuffer**\n\nsolution\n\n<pre>\n  StringBuffer sentence = new StringBuffer();\n  for (String w : words){\n    sentence.append(w);\n  }\n  return sentence.toString();\n  //StringBuffer simply creates array of all the //strings,copy them back to a string only one time\n</pre>\n\nIt looks like php function explode\n\n<pre>\n  //$set is an array\n  $words=explode(\' \',$set);\n</pre>\n\n\nthese two method both use String one time .\n\nif iterate String array , the String sentence would be copied and updated\n\n\nStringBuffer and php explode() did can help you avoid this problem .\n',3,'2016-11-07 07:15:27','2016-11-07 07:18:05',1,'2016-11-07 07:18:05',NULL),(42,'HashMap related methods','hashmap-related-methods','Summary and Usage ',' **HashMap<K,V>**\n\nK is key , V is value \n\nK and V can both be define to Integer and String \n\nMap<Integer,Integer> map = new HashMap<>();\n\n**Method Summary **\n\n**clear():** Removes all of the mappings from this map. return type is void . \n\n**containsKey(Object  key )** & **containsValue(Object value )**: \n\nReturns true if this map maps one or more keys(values)  to the specified value.\n\n**get(Object key)** :   Returns the value to which the specified key is mapped, or null if this map contains no mapping for the key.\n\n**isEmpty()** :  Returns true if this map contains no key-value mappings.\n\n**put(K,V)**  :  Associates the specified value with the specified key in this map.\n\n**	remove(Object key)** :  Removes the mapping for the specified key from this map if present.',3,'2016-11-08 05:16:40','2016-11-08 05:33:47',1,'2016-11-08 05:20:27',NULL),(43,'Arrays','arrays','Basic Syntax and Method ','**What is Array in Java ?**\n\nJava provides a data structure, the array, which stores a *fixed-size* sequential collection of elements of the same type. \n\n**Declaring Array Variables Syntax **\n<pre>\n<code>\ndataType[] arrayName;   // priority \n//or\ndataType arrayName[];  // works also \n</code>\n</pre>\n\n**Example **\n\n<pre>\nint[] numbers;\n//or\nint numbers[];\n</pre>\n\n**Creating Arrays Syntax **\n\n<pre>\nnumbers= new int[10];\n</pre>\n\nDeclaring an array variable, creating an array, and assigning the reference of the array to the variable can be combined in one statement\n\n<pre>\nint[] numbers = new int[10];\n//Alternatively you can create arrays as follows\nint[] numbers (opitional name) = {value0, value1, ..., valuek};\n</pre>\n\nThe array elements are accessed through the index. Array indices are 0-based; that is, they start from 0 to numbers.length-1.',3,'2016-11-08 06:26:02','2016-11-08 06:46:47',1,'2016-11-08 06:29:12',NULL),(45,'Wonder Woman Trailer II Breakdown','wonder-woman-trailer-ii-breakdown','【預告解析】神力女超人|神奇女俠|預告解說|預告分析|萬人迷電影院| Wonder Woman trailer breakdown','<iframe width=100% height=\"560\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/4ei_AYflraA\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',3,'2016-11-08 06:56:33','2016-11-08 06:58:47',1,'2016-11-08 06:58:47',NULL),(46,'Wonder Woman Trailer Analysis II','wonder-woman-trailer-analysis-ii','《神力女超人 Wonder Woman》第二部預告．預告分析(二)','<iframe width=100% height=\"560\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Z7Nyv02jt8w\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',3,'2016-11-08 07:04:16','2016-11-08 07:05:56',1,'2016-11-08 07:05:56',NULL),(47,'Wonder Woman Trailer Analysis I','wonder-woman-trailer-analysis-i','《神力女超人 Wonder Woman》第二部預告．預告分析(一)','<iframe width=100% height=560 src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/fjSUMYOSRjI\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',3,'2016-11-08 07:09:26','2016-11-08 07:10:31',1,'2016-11-08 07:10:31',NULL),(48,'Resident Evil 6: The Final Chapter ALL Trailer & Clips (2017)','resident-evil-6-the-final-chapter-all-trailer-clips-2017','Trailer & Clips (2017)','<iframe width=100% height=\"560\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/FPdbc3XAjfE\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',3,'2016-11-10 22:02:36','2016-11-10 22:05:28',1,'2016-11-10 22:05:28',NULL),(49,' Logan Wolverine 3 Trailer Analysis','logan-wolverine-3-trailer-analysis','【預告分析】羅根|盧根|金鋼狼3|預告解析|預告解說|角色介紹|萬人迷電影院| LOGAN trailer analysis','<iframe width=100% height=\"560\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/zdUU2BLVvLU\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',3,'2016-11-10 22:06:19','2016-11-10 22:10:29',1,'2016-11-10 22:10:29',NULL),(53,'Valid Palindrome NO 125','valid-palindrome-no-125','Java Solution ','# Question\n\n**Given a string, determine if it is a palindrome, considering only alphanumeric characters and ignoring cases.**\n\n# For example\n**\"A man, a plan, a canal: Panama\" is a palindrome.\n\"race a car\" is not a palindrome.**\n\n# Note:\n**Have you consider that the string might be empty? This is a good question to ask during an interview.**\n\n**For the purpose of this problem, we define empty string as valid palindrome.**\n\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\">1:  public class Solution {  \n2:    public boolean isPalindrome(String s) {  \n3:      int i =0; j=s.length()-1;  \n4:      while(i&lt;j){  \n5:       while(i&lt;j&amp;&amp;!Character.isLetterOrDigit(s.charAt(i))) i++;  \n6:       while(i&lt;j&amp;&amp;!Character.isLetterOrDigit(s.charAt(j))) j--;  \n7:       if(Character.toLowerCase(i))!=Character.toLowerCase(j)){  \n8:         return false;  \n9:       }else{  \n10:        i++;j--;  \n11:       }  \n12:      }  \n13:      return true;  \n14:    }  \n15:  }  \n</code></pre>\n',3,'2016-11-17 04:09:53','2016-11-22 06:33:00',1,'2016-11-17 04:13:44',NULL),(55,'Single Number NO 136','single-number-no-136','Java Solution ','# Question\n\n**Given an array of integers, every element appears twice except for one. Find that single one.**\n\n# **Note:**\n\n**Your algorithm should have a linear runtime complexity. Could you implement it without using extra memory?**\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\"> public int singleNumber(int[] nums) {  \n   int res=0;  \n   for(int i=0;i&lt;nums.length;i++){  \n     res^=nums[i];  \n   }  \n   return res;  \n }  \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-19 03:57:59','2016-11-22 06:32:44',1,'2016-11-19 04:00:45',NULL),(56,'Climbing Stairs NO 70','climbing-stairs-no-70','Java Solution ','# Question:\n**You are climbing a staircase. It takes n steps to reach to the top.\nEach time you can either climb 1 or 2 steps. In how many distinct ways can you climb to\nthe top?**\n\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\">1:  public int climbStairs(int n) {  \n2:      int p=1, q=1;  \n3:      for(int i=2;i&lt;=n;i++){  \n4:        int tmp=q;  \n5:        q+=p;  \n6:        p=tmp;  \n7:      }  \n8:      return q;  \n9:  }  \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-19 06:25:04','2016-11-19 06:27:26',1,'2016-11-19 06:27:26',NULL),(57,'Power of Two NO 231','power-of-two-no-231','Java Solution ','# Question\n\n**Given an integer, write a function to determine if it is a power of two.**\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\">1:   public boolean isPowerOfTwo(int n) {  \n2:      return n &gt; 0 &amp;&amp; ((n &amp; (n - 1)) == 0 );  \n3:   }    \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-19 07:06:41','2016-11-22 06:32:04',1,'2016-11-19 07:08:12',NULL),(58,'Implement Strstr NO 28','implement-strstr-no-28','Java Solution ','# Question\n\n**Returns the index of the first occurrence of needle in haystack, or -1 if needle is not part of haystack.**\n\n# Check Point \n**1. int i is the position in the haystack.**\n\n**2. int j is the position in the noodle , every position in haystack , we will try to match whether noodle is part of haystack. **\n\n**3. the limit is the haystack length , when i+j equal haystack length , which means previous part not matched and rest ones neither . (-1)**\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\">1:  public int strStr(String haystack, String needle) {  \n2:    for (int i = 0; ; i++) {  \n3:     for (int j = 0; ; j++) {  \n4:      if (j == needle.length()) return i;  \n5:      if (i + j == haystack.length()) return -1;  \n6:      if (needle.charAt(j) != haystack.charAt(i + j)) break;  \n7:     }  \n8:   }  \n9:  }  \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-20 02:53:14','2016-11-22 06:31:47',1,'2016-11-20 02:55:26',NULL),(59,'Reverse Words in a String NO 151','reverse-words-in-a-string','Java Solution','# Question\n\n**Given an input string, reverse the string word by word.**\n\n# For example,\n**Given s = \"the sky is blue\",**\n\n**return \"blue is sky the\".**\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\">1:  public String reverseWords(String s) {  \n2:    StringBuilder reversed = new StringBuilder();  \n3:    int j = s.length();  \n4:    for (int i = s.length() - 1; i &gt;= 0; i--) {  \n5:     if (s.charAt(i) == \' \') {  \n6:       j = i;  \n7:     } else if (i == 0 || s.charAt(i - 1) == \' \') {  \n8:       if (reversed.length() != 0) {  \n9:        reversed.append(\' \');  \n10:       }  \n11:       reversed.append(s.substring(i, j));  \n12:     }  \n13:    }  \n14:    return reversed.toString();  \n15:  }  \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-20 08:19:23','2016-11-22 06:31:21',1,'2016-11-20 08:20:52',NULL),(60,'Valid Number NO 65','valid-number-no-65','Java Solution ','# Question\n\n**Validate if a given string is numeric.**\n\n# Some examples:\n**\"0\" => true**\n\n**\" 0.1 \" => true**\n\n**\"abc\" => false**\n\n**\"1 a\" => false**\n\n**\"2e10\" => true**\n\n# Note:\n\n**It is intended for the problem statement to be ambiguous. You should gather all requirements up front before implementing one.**\n\n# Check Point \n\n**1. check the space in the begining and end (isWhitespace) . **\n\n**2. check the number is positive or negative . **\n\n**3. check whether number has dot . Like +.034 , -0.1 etc . **\n\n**4. check whether number contain an optional exponent part , make sure previous part is numberic and only have one e  and numbers in the rest part . If number has exponent part , the number could not have dot (.) in the rest . But +0.1e23 is acceptable. **\n\n**5. remember check the space in the end . **\n\n**6. make sure all the position in the String is checked . **\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\">1:  public boolean isNumber(String s) {  \n2:      int i=0,n=s.length();  \n3:      while(i&lt;n&amp;&amp;Character.isWhitespace(s.charAt(i))) i++;  \n4:      if(i&lt;n&amp;&amp;(s.charAt(i)==\'+\'||s.charAt(i)==\'-\')) i++;  \n5:      boolean isNumeric=false;  \n6:      while(i&lt;n&amp;&amp;Character.isDigit(s.charAt(i))){  \n7:        i++;  \n8:        isNumeric=true;  \n9:      }  \n10:      if(i&lt;n&amp;&amp;s.charAt(i)==\'.\'){  \n11:        i++;  \n12:        while(i&lt;n&amp;&amp;Character.isDigit(s.charAt(i))){  \n13:          i++;  \n14:          isNumeric=true;  \n15:        }  \n16:      }  \n17:      if(isNumeric&amp;&amp;i&lt;n&amp;&amp;s.charAt(i)==\'e\'){  \n18:        i++;  \n19:        isNumeric=false;  \n20:        if(i&lt;n&amp;&amp;(s.charAt(i)==\'+\'||s.charAt(i)==\'-\')) i++;  \n21:        while(i&lt;n&amp;&amp;Character.isDigit(s.charAt(i))){  \n22:          i++;  \n23:          isNumeric=true;  \n24:        }  \n25:      }  \n26:      while(i&lt;n&amp;&amp;Character.isWhitespace(s.charAt(i))) i++;  \n27:      return isNumeric&amp;&amp;i==n;  \n28:  }  \n</code></pre>\n\n**Github:** https://github.com/Jerrrrry/leetcode/blob/master/valid_number_65.java',3,'2016-11-21 02:25:50','2016-11-22 06:31:07',1,'2016-11-21 02:27:54',NULL),(61,'Fizz Buzz NO 412','fizz-buzz','Java Solution ','# Question\n\n**Write a program that outputs the string representation of numbers from 1 to n.**\n\n**But for multiples of three it should output “Fizz” instead of the number and for the multiples of five output “Buzz”. **\n\n**For numbers which are multiples of both three and five output “FizzBuzz”.**\n\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\">1:  public List&lt;String&gt; fizzBuzz(int n) {  \n2:      List&lt;String&gt; result = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();  \n3:      for (int i = 1; i &lt;= n; i++) {  \n4:        if (i % 3 == 0 &amp;&amp; i % 5 == 0) result.add(\"FizzBuzz\");  \n5:        else if (i % 3 == 0) result.add(\"Fizz\");  \n6:        else if (i % 5 == 0) result.add(\"Buzz\");  \n7:        else result.add(String.valueOf(i));  \n8:      }  \n9:      return result;  \n10:   }  \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-21 04:50:17','2016-11-22 06:30:51',1,'2016-11-21 04:52:22',NULL),(62,'Roman to Integer NO 13','roman-to-integer-no-13','Java Solution ','# Question\n\n**Given a roman numeral, convert it to an integer.**\n\n**Input is guaranteed to be within the range from 1 to 3999.**\n\n# Solution \n**if current letter number is greater than previous number , then subtract the previous number and add current number , considering we have add previous number before . So we need subtract the previous number twice **\n\n**if current number is less than previous number , we normally add the current number **\n\n# Code\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\"> private Map&lt;Character,Integer&gt; map=new HashMap&lt;Character,Integer&gt;(){  \n  {  \n   put(\'I\',1);put(\'V\',5);put(\'X\',10);put(\'L\',50);put(\'C\',100);  \n   put(\'D\',500);put(\'M\',1000);  \n  }  \n };  \n public int romanToInt(String s){  \n  int prev=0,total=0;  \n  for(char c:s.toCharArray()){  \n   int curr=map.get(c);  \n   total+=(curr&gt;prev)?(curr-2*prev):curr;  \n   prev=curr;  \n  }  \n  return total;  \n }  \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-22 06:24:03','2016-11-22 06:30:36',1,'2016-11-22 06:29:05',NULL),(63,'Java Stack Class Usage','java-stack-class-usage','Normal Method ','# Method & Description \n\n**1. boolean empty()**\n\nTests if this stack is empty. Returns true if the stack is empty, and returns false if the stack contains elements.\n\n**2. Object peek()**\n\nReturns the element on the top of the stack, but does not remove it.\n\n**3. Object pop()**\n\nReturns the element on the top of the stack, removing it in the process.\n\n**4. Object push(Object element)**\n\nPushes the element onto the stack. Element is also returned.\n\nNew element would be push to the top , although it will show [1,2,3....,latest_element], but when you pop(), it will auto remove the latest as top element. \n\n**5. int search (Object element)**\n\nSearches for element in the stack. If found, its offset from the top of the stack is returned. Otherwise, .1 is returned.',3,'2016-11-23 01:34:39','2016-11-23 01:48:23',1,'2016-11-23 01:42:34',NULL),(64,'Valid Parentheses NO 20','valid-parentheses-no-20','Java Solution ','# Question \n\n**Given a string containing just the characters \'(\', \')\', \'{\', \'}\', \'[\' and \']\', determine if the input string is valid.**\n\n**The brackets must close in the correct order, \"()\" and \"()[]{}\" are all valid but \"(]\" and \"([)]\" are not.**\n\n# Solution \n\n**if \'({[\' is in the string , then mark them , and check next has matched symbol **\n\n**By the way when we use Character , need define like char test=\'test\';**\n\n**if \"Test\" would be the string type . **\n\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\"> public boolean isValidParentheses(String s){  \n  Stack&lt;Character&gt; stack=new Stack&lt;Character&gt;();  \n  for(Character c:s.toCharArray()){  \n   if(\"({[\".contains(String.valueOf(c))){  \n    stack.push(c);  \n   }else{  \n    if(!stack.isEmpty()&amp;&amp;is_valid(stack.peek(),c)){  \n     stack.pop();  \n    }else{  \n     return false;  \n    }  \n   }  \n  }  \n  return stack.isEmpty();  \n }  \n private boolean is_valid(char c1,char c2){  \n  return (c1==\'(\'&amp;&amp;c2==\')\')||(c1==\'[\'&amp;&amp;c2==\']\')||(c1==\'[\'&amp;&amp;c2==\']\');  \n }  \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-23 06:18:45','2016-11-23 06:22:53',1,'2016-11-23 06:22:53',NULL),(65,'Merge Two Sorted List NO 21','merge-two-sorted-list-no-21','Java Solution ','# Question \n\n**Merge two sorted linked lists and return it as a new list. The new list should **\n\n**be made by splicing together the nodes of the first two lists.**\n\n# Solution\n** Compare two Lists till the end  **\n\n# Code\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\"> public ListNode mergeTwoLists(ListNode l1,ListNode l2){  \n  ListNode dummy=new ListNode(0);  \n  ListNode lastNode=dummy;  \n  while(l1!=null&amp;&amp;l2!=null){  \n   if(l1.val&lt;l2.val){  \n    lastNode.next=l1;  \n    l1=l1.next;  \n   }else{  \n    lastNode.next=12;  \n    l2=l2.next;  \n   }  \n   lastNode=lastNode.next;  \n  }  \n  if(l1!=null){  \n   lastNode.next=l1;  \n  }else{  \n   lastNode.next=l2;  \n  }  \n  return dummy.next;  \n }  \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-23 07:31:34','2016-11-23 07:37:15',1,'2016-11-23 07:37:15',NULL),(66,'Swap Nodes in Pairs NO 24','swap-nodes-in-pairs-no-24','Java Solution ','# Question \n**Given a linked list, swap every two adjacent nodes and return its head.**\n\n**For example,**\n\n**Given 1->2->3->4, you should return the list as 2->1->4->3.**\n\n**Your algorithm should use only constant space. You may not modify the values in the list, only nodes itself can be changed.**\n\n# Code\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\"> public ListNode swapPairs(ListNode head){  \n  ListNode original=new ListNode(0);  \n  original.next=head;  \n  head=original;  \n  //  \n  while(head.next!=null&amp;&amp;head.next.next!=null){  \n   ListNode n1=head.next,n2=head.next.next;  \n   head.next=n2;  \n   n1.next=n2.next;  \n   n2.next=n1;  \n   head=n1;  \n  }  \n  return original.next;  \n }  \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-23 22:13:18','2016-11-23 22:15:47',1,'2016-11-23 22:15:47',NULL),(67,'Length of Last Word NO 58','length-of-last-word-no-58','Java Solution ','# Question\n\n**Given a string s consists of upper/lower-case alphabets and empty space characters \' \', return the length of last word in the string.**\n\n**If the last word does not exist, return 0.**\n\n# Note:\n\n**A word is defined as a character sequence consists of non-space characters only.**\n\n# For example, \n\n**Given s = \"Hello World\",**\n\n**return 5.**\n\n# Code\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\"> public int lengthOdLastWord(String s){  \n  if(s==null) return 0;  \n  s=s.trim();  \n  if(s.length()==0) return 0;  \n  String[] words=s.split(\" \");  \n  return words[words.length-1].length();  \n }  \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-30 02:14:40','2016-11-30 02:18:27',1,'2016-11-30 02:18:27',NULL),(68,'Remove Duplicates from Sorted List NO 83','remove-duplicates-from-sorted-list-no-83','Java Solution ','# Question\n\n**Given a sorted linked list, delete all duplicates such that each element appear only once.**\n\n# For example,\n\n**Given 1->1->2, return 1->2.**\n\n**Given 1->1->2->3->3, return 1->2->3.**\n\n# Code\n\n<pre  style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:12px;border:1px dashed #CCCCCC;width:99%;height:auto;overflow:auto;background:#f0f0f0;;background-image:URL(http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_z5ltvMQPaa8/SjJXr_U2YBI/AAAAAAAAAAM/46OqEP32CJ8/s320/codebg.gif);padding:0px;color:#000000;text-align:left;line-height:20px;\"><code style=\"color:#000000;word-wrap:normal;\"> public ListNode deleteDuplicates(ListNode head){  \n  if(head==null) return null;  \n  ListNode node=head;  \n  while(node.next!=null){  \n   if(node.val==node.next.val){  \n    node.next=node.next.next;  \n   }else{  \n    node=node.next;  \n   }  \n  }  \n  return head;  \n }  \n</code></pre>',3,'2016-11-30 02:46:18','2016-11-30 02:49:37',1,'2016-11-30 02:48:44',NULL);
